Rating: 3
I used 2 cups of all-flour and 1 cup of wheat flour, and replaced the butter with 1/2 cup canola oil and 1/4 cup melted butter. Also, as other reviewers suggested, I separated the eggs, beat the egg whites stiff, and folded them under the batter. All in all, the waffles were tasty but came out quite heavy. I also made the apple and dried fruit compote, which turned out very nicely.

Rating: 4
Usually make the Cornmeal Buttermilk "Nesbitt" recipe here for waffles but wanted to try something different. Did not make the toppings here - we were craving waffles, bacon and maple syrup. These were great, made with a few changes just for kicks. For dry ingredients I used 2 cups all-purpose flour, 1/2 cup whole wheat flour and 1/2 cup cornmeal. For the wet I used 3 cups buttermilk, 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup canola oil. Results were fantastic, light crisp airy and wonderful waffles. My waffle- maker made exactly 16 4x4 thick waffles. Will definitely make again!

