Rating: 4
Terrific waffle recipe! Our guests always rave about them. A tip to make this recipe even better is to separate the egg yolks and whites. Add the slightly beaten yolks when the recipes says to add the eggs. Then beat the whites with a mixer until firm peaks form. Then fold the whites into the batter. This will lighten the waffles a bit - creating a terrific texture.

Rating: 3
I made these waffles for Christmas breakfast this year. They were a big hit; light, crispy, and held up well under a lot of maple syrup (we didn't make the toppings). To make life easy I made them ahead. They froze well and reheated in 350 degree oven for 5-7 minutes without any problem. Will do again next year.

